%N A394405 Number of transitive relations, on an n-set, that are not quasi-orders.
%C A394405 A quasi-order is a relation that is both transitive and reflexive.
%C A394405 a(n) is the number by which the number of transitive relations exceeds the number of quasi-orders.
%F A394405 a(n) = A006905(n) - A000798(n).
%e A394405 On a 1-set, X={x}, the only relation that is transitive but not reflexive (or a quasi-order) is the empty relation, thus, a(1)=1.
%Y A394405 Cf. A000798, A006905.
%K A394405 nonn,hard,new
